    Example Vascular Plant Cover data

    VascPlantEx.Rd

    A dataset containing vascular plant data for use in vascPlantMets() example.

    VascPlantEx

    Format

    A data frame with 1200 observations on the following 6 variables.

    UID

    A unique site visit ID

    STATE

    Two letter state code of sample site

    USAC_REGION

    US Army Corps region of sample site

    PLOT

    Plot number of measurement

    USDA_NAME

    Taxon name corresponding to input taxa tables

    COVER

    A numeric vector representing the percent cover of a taxon within a plot

    Note

    This dataset is a small subset of actual NWCA 2011 data, with UIDs recoded.

    Examples

    head(VascPlantEx)
#>   UID STATE USAC_REGION PLOT             USDA_NAME COVER
#> 1   7    FL  CSTL_PLAIN    2 SAGITTARIA LANCIFOLIA    28
#> 2   7    FL  CSTL_PLAIN    3 SAGITTARIA LANCIFOLIA     6
#> 3   7    FL  CSTL_PLAIN    4 SAGITTARIA LANCIFOLIA     5
#> 4   7    FL  CSTL_PLAIN    5 SAGITTARIA LANCIFOLIA    20
#> 5   7    FL  CSTL_PLAIN    5       SPARTINA PATENS     0
#> 6   7    FL  CSTL_PLAIN    1      PANICUM VIRGATUM     0
str(VascPlantEx)
#> 'data.frame':	1200 obs. of  6 variables:
#>  $ UID        : int  7 7 7 7 7 7 7 7 7 7 ...
#>  $ STATE      : chr  "FL" "FL" "FL" "FL" ...
#>  $ USAC_REGION: chr  "CSTL_PLAIN" "CSTL_PLAIN" "CSTL_PLAIN" "CSTL_PLAIN" ...
#>  $ PLOT       : int  2 3 4 5 5 1 4 5 1 1 ...
#>  $ USDA_NAME  : chr  "SAGITTARIA LANCIFOLIA" "SAGITTARIA LANCIFOLIA" "SAGITTARIA LANCIFOLIA" "SAGITTARIA LANCIFOLIA" ...
#>  $ COVER      : num  28 6 5 20 0 0 1 1 6 6 ...
